{"questionId":"9074615","questionHtml":"<p>Wind of speed <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> flows through a wind generator. The wind speed drops to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math> after passing through the blades. What is the maximum possible efficiency of the generator?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>19</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>26</mn><mn>27</mn></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074615","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.28","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Wind of speed v flows through a wind generator. The wind speed drops to v3 after passing through the blades. What is the maximum possible efficiency of the generator? A. 127 B. 827","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"28","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Energy production","8.1 – Energy sources","Core","Topic 8: Energy production"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}